Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with resource allocation and power control in a two-user downlink NOMA system, which is a common topic in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a communication system (NOMA) that is relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper uses optimization techniques to obtain the optimal resource allocation, which is a common topic in systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the trade-offs between different performance metrics (sum-rate, user fairness, delay-limited throughput), which are relevant to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses analytical and simulation methods to analyze the performance of the NOMA system, which is relevant to computational engineering.
